result.text:
#XiStory

Ahead of a banquet on Wednesday, US President Joe Biden showed President Xi Jinping his phone, inviting the Chinese leader's attention to the screen.
​
"Do you know this young man?" Biden asked.

"Yes, that was me 38 years ago," said Xi, with a knowing smile.

The image displayed on Biden's phone was a photo Xi took in 1985 when he was on his maiden trip to the US.

San Francisco was the first stop of Xi's trip. Much like any other city visitor, Xi had his picture taken with the Golden Gate Bridge.

At that time, Xi, in his early thirties, was a county leader of Zhengding in China's northern province of Hebei.

"You haven't changed a bit!" said Biden with a chuckle, drawing a burst of cheerful laughter.

Amid such lighthearted ambiance, the two leaders stepped into the banquet hall together.
